    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/activity/mesh-independence-study",
    "type": "VerificationActivity",
    "name": "Mesh Independence Study for CBP CFD Model",
    "description": "A systematic mesh refinement study was conducted across three levels of spatial discretization (coarse: 2.1M cells, medium: 5.8M cells, fine: 14.3M cells) to demonstrate solution independence for the primary quantity of interest (relative hemolysis index RH). Richardson extrapolation was applied to quantify the grid convergence index (GCI) at each operating point. All five flow-speed combinations were evaluated. The study confirmed that the medium mesh achieves GCI < 1.2% for RH predictions, satisfying the discretization error acceptance criterion.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementVerification",
    "performedBy": "https://uofa.net/synth/org/morrison-lab",
    "startedAtTime": "2025-09-10T08:00:00Z",
